      "writtenOn": "2019-08-01T20:46:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Is the concern that having such a tag would could be confusing as the image contains more changes than the image tag?\n\nVadim also mentioned the naming scheme of `\u003cdate\u003e_\u003ccommitposition\u003e_\u003ccommit\u003e`, which sgtm (modulo not knowing off the top of my head where to fetch the commit position) but also doesn\u0027t accommodate local non-committed changes.\n\nWhat if we included e.g. \"-tainted\" in the tag if there are local non-committed changes?",
