      "writtenOn": "2019-08-01T22:14:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Is the concern that having such a tag would could be confusing as the image contains more changes than the image tag?\n\nyes, because it would be a lie\n\nfor `\u003cdate\u003e_\u003ccommitposition\u003e_\u003ccommit\u003e`, I am pretty sure that is in the context of continuously built images on CI, will be implemented in some common place (agnostic to specific services) by Vadim. This implementation won\u0027t be used for that.\n\nadding -tainted if there are local changes is not that trivial: https://cs.chromium.org/chromium/infra/luci/appengine/components/tools/calculate_version.py?type\u003dcs\u0026q\u003dcalculate_version\u0026sq\u003dpackage:chromium\u0026g\u003d0\u0026l\u003d108\nso I am not sure we can do it easily, moreso in bash. I tried running `gae.py version` but it requires an dir with an appengine app.\n\nalways adding -tainted seems to be the best option so far",
      "parentUuid": "6dd757ce_302aa478",
